<%@ Page Title="Privacy Policy" Language="C#" MasterPageFile="~/usersite.Master" AutoEventWireup="true" CodeFile="PrivacyPolicy.aspx.cs" Inherits="ecommerce_mlm.PrivacyPolicy" %>

<asp:Content ID="Content1" ContentPlaceHolderID="head" runat="server">
</asp:Content>

<asp:Content ID="Content2" ContentPlaceHolderID="ContentPlaceHolder1" runat="server">
    <div class="dashboard-breadcrumb">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="dashboard-breadcrumb-inner">
                <div class="breadcrumb-left">
                    <h3>Privacy Policy</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="breadcrumb-right">
                    <a href="index.aspx"><i class="fas fa-home"></i></a>
                    <span> / Privacy Policy</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container" style="margin-top:40px;">
        <div class="standard-content-box">
            <h1 style="color:#1e293b; font-weight:800; margin:0 0 10px; font-size:2.2rem;">Privacy Directive</h1>
            <p style="font-size:1.1rem; color:#64748b; margin-bottom:40px;">How we govern, sanitize and secure your sensory identity datasets.</p>
            <hr style="border:0; border-top:1px solid #f1f5f9; margin-bottom:40px;" />
            <h2>Data Collection Paradigms</h2>
            <p>We partition collection into two critical vectors: (1) Explicit Identity variables needed for logistical fulfillment (Name, Geometry Coordinates, Financial Route) and (2) Algorithmic Aggregations aimed at optimizing session interfaces via non-identifiable heuristics.</p>
            
            <h2>Disclosure Matrix</h2>
            <p>Your datasets reside securely on containerized persistent blocks. We strictly prohibit arbitrary secondary commercial data syndication. Access vectors are restricted to essential operational logistics partners (Couriers/Gateways) only on a rigid need-to-evaluate perimeter restriction.</p>

            <h2>Cookie Hygiene</h2>
            <p>Our instances execute essential micro-caching tokens purely to maintain persistent login cycles and dynamically preserve cart state transitions. No persistent behavioral tracking pixels are activated unilaterally without user prompt validation.</p>

            <h2>Retention Boundaries</h2>
            <p>Records persist precisely for the operational lifecycle designated by regulatory auditing statutes. Post account termination, sensitive operational variables are purged following a static 48-hour cooling buffer.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</asp:Content>
